Hello and welcome back to my blog, where I'll be sharing my exciting journey as an Outreachy intern working 
on the OpenRefine project, “improve how designers can meaningfully contribute to OpenRefine” 

If you’re not new here, then you most definitely are familiar with my excitement about OpenRefine as I’ve 
written about it in my previous blog posts during the contribution phase of my Outreachy application. 

So you can understand that I'm absolutely buzzing to have this opportunity to contribute my UI/UX design 
skills to such an impactful project and software. So, grab a cup of your favorite beverage, and let’s do this!

Firstly let’s explore some of my core values:

Kindness: In a world that often feels chaotic, I believe that kindness can make a significant difference. Whether 
it's a small act of compassion or lending a listening ear, kindness has the power to create positive ripples
in our lives and those around us.

Curiosity: Curiosity has been my constant companion, propelling me to explore the wonders of the world. It has led 
me down exciting paths, from uncovering hidden corners of nature through sunset photography to diving into the 
depths of design possibilities. 

Humor: I love infusing humor into my interactions, projects, and everyday life. It adds a dash of lightheartedness
and reminds us not to lose sight of the joy that surrounds us. In this blog, expect witty anecdotes, funny 
design mishaps, and a sprinkle of laughter to brighten your day.

