Beyond my love for design and technology, I have a few unique interests that shape my perspective and approach to 
problem-solving. For instance, I find solace in sad music, which, strangely enough, fuels my creativity. The 
emotions captured in those melodies inspire me to create meaningful and impactful designs.

Photography is another passion of mine, especially capturing breathtaking sunset moments. The beauty of nature 
reminds me of the importance of aesthetics in design and the power of creating experiences that evoke positive emotions.

Lastly, I love writing newsletters to my friends. This creative outlet not only allows me to communicate with my loved 
ones but also helps me practice concise storytelling, which is essential for effective UX design.


Last year, when I first learned about Outreachy,  I embarked on a journey to contribute to the Open Life Science project 
as an Outreachy applicant. Although I didn't make it past the contribution phase, that experience only fueled my 
determination to try again. The passion for design, combined with my desire to make a meaningful impact in open source, 
made me to apply for the Outreachy program once more, this time with OpenRefine and May the 4th, 2023 will go 
down as one the best days of my life.

I hope you stick around as I’m required to blog every 2 weeks on my journey. See yu soon.
